-- Asia Private Equity Weekly News, July 7, 2014
-- 
-- Mon Jul 07, 2014 04:45AM EDT
-- None



July 7 (Reuters) - News and developments in Asia private equity from Reuters News for the week ended July 4.

JULY 3 GLOBAL PRIVATE equity firm TPG Capital [TPG.UL] is buying a stake in Hong Kong-based hedge fund sponsor HS Group Ltd (HSG) and establishing a strategic relationship with the company, HSG said. [ID:nL4N0PE2RG]  INDIA'S RENEW Power Ventures Pvt Ltd has raised $140 million from three investors, including a private equity fund managed by Goldman Sachs <GS.N>, the renewable energy firm said. [ID:nL4N0PE2J2]  CHAMP PRIVATE Equity has agreed a deal to sell industrial transport company LCR Group to rival buyout firm Archer Capital for about A$200 million, after a logistics business which had an option to buy LCR failed to bid, a source familiar with the deal told Reuters. [ID:nL4N0PE13P] A PLANNED law allowing foreign firms to take full control of Philippine lenders is drawing eager suitors to the sector, including Japan's Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group <8306.T> and Malaysia's CIMB Group Holdings <CIMB.KL>, bankers familiar with the matter say. [ID:nL4N0P82RY]   JULY 2 CHINA'S HUAXIA Dairy Farm Ltd said it has received $106 million in investment capital from a consortium led by Singapore sovereign wealth fund GIC [GIC.UL] and private equity firm Olympus Capital, to expand its farming operations and retail dairy business. [ID:nL4N0PD17S]  PRIVATE EQUITY firm CVC Capital Partners Ltd [CVC.UL] has hired Credit Suisse, Deutsche Bank and Goldman Sachs to handle a share sale in Indonesian internet service provider PT Link Net Tbk <LINK.JK>, which could raise at least $500 million, people familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL4N0PD16C] CITIC CAPITAL Partners, the private equity arm of CITIC Capital Holdings Ltd, said it had acquired U.S. dental company DDS LAB LLC on undisclosed terms. [ID:nL4N0PD2CZ]  BEIJING DIGITAL Telecom, China's largest mobile telecom retail chain and backed by 3i Group Plc, CDH Holding and Crown Flame, has raised HK$883.3 million ($114 million) from its IPO, IFR reported.JULY 1 SHARES IN Club Mediterranee <CMIP.PA> rose 10 percent after a new takeover offer by top shareholder Andrea Bonomi fuelled hopes of a bidding war for control of the French resort operator. [ID:nL6N0PC3H4] FRANCE AND China have launched a midcap private equity fund to boost investment and exposure between the two following a visit by the Chinese president to France earlier this year. [ID:nL6N0PB2MR]   JUNE 30 U.S. PRIVATE equity giants TPG and Carlyle Group <CG.O> aim to raise up to A$2.57 billion ($2.42 billion) by listing Australian hospital operator Healthscope Ltd, in what is shaping up as the country's third-largest initial public offering. [ID:nL4N0PB052]  ABRAAJ GROUP has mandated Citigroup <C.N> to evaluate options for its indirect stake in Pakistani utility K-Electric <KELE.KA>, the Dubai-based private equity firm said on Monday. [ID:nL6N0PB1UO]